789
00:48:44,406 --> 00:48:45,706
But it can't give you all the answers.

790
00:48:45,887 --> 00:48:48,607
So there's still a lot of manual labor

791
00:48:48,727 --> 00:48:52,269
and experimentation involved to find the right.

792
00:48:53,729 --> 00:48:58,651
solutions. So, also a box should kind of like always be a little bit flexible.

793
00:48:59,411 --> 00:49:05,454
A box art is like if your rules are too rigid, you kind of get unreceptive for natural growth

794
00:49:05,554 --> 00:49:10,536
and opportunities. So, for example, one of the rules is we have no text in the game, but we

795
00:49:10,576 --> 00:49:15,238
actually broke that rule a little bit because we have these bits and pieces of French flavor text

796
00:49:15,278 --> 00:49:18,339
that we're never going to translate. It's just on signs and things like that.

797
00:49:20,220 --> 00:49:24,164
So, and goals and constraints usually work best

798
00:49:24,204 --> 00:49:25,465
when they complement each other.

799
00:49:25,846 --> 00:49:29,629
So, constraints that contradict each other

800
00:49:29,689 --> 00:49:32,932
will stay contradictory up until the release of your game.

